headlines.description: — Jalen Duren had 23 points and 15 rebounds as the Detroit Pistons overcame a career-high 51 points from Zach LaVine to beat the Chicago Bulls 118-102 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine's 51 points not enough for Bulls in 118-102 loss to Pistons

headlines.description: — The Washington Wizards were already facing a bit of a gut check after allowing 143 points in their season opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards bounce back defensively, top winless Grizzlies 113-106 for victory in home opener

events.name: New York Knicks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram poured in an array of mid-range pullups, turnarounds and fades. Zion Williamson kept finding ways to power toward the rim and finish with touch.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram scores 26, Williamson adds 24 as Pelicans top Knicks 96-87

headlines.description: — Aaron Nesmith scored a career-high 26 points and Tyrese Haliburton had 21 points, 13 assists and eight rebounds, sending the Indiana Pacers to a 125-113 victory over the short-handed Cleveland Cavaliers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Aaron Nesmith has 26 points for the Pacers in a 125-113 win over the Donovan Mitchell-less Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid and Tyrese Maxey each scored 34 points, and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Toronto Raptors 114-107 on Saturday night to give new coach Nick Nurse his first win against his former team.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid and Maxey each score 34, 76ers beat Raptors 114-107 to give Nurse first win

headlines.description: — Naz Reid relished the roar from the Minnesota crowd roar during introductions and the fast chant of his name late in the game, further affirmation he's in the right place even though he comes off the bench.
headlines.shortLinkText: Naz Reid leads Timberwolves in 106-90 takedown of short-handed Heat in home opener

headlines.description: — Grayson Allen cut into the lane before rising up and flushing an unexpected one-handed jam in traffic, pushing the Phoenix lead to 30 points midway through the third quarter.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant scores 26 points as the Suns easily handle the Jazz 126-104
